SIMPLE: usual
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Usual
<hw>U"su*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>usualis</ets>, from <ets>usus</ets> use: cf. F. <ets>usuel</ets>.
See <er>Use</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>Such as is in common use;
such as occurs in ordinary practice, or in the ordinary course of
events; customary; ordinary; habitual; common.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Consultation with oracles was a thing very <qex>usual</qex> and
frequent in their times.</q> <rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We can make friends of these <qex>usual</qex> enemies.</q>
<rj><qau>Baxter.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>U"su*al*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>U"su*al*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Usucaption</ent>⟦br⟧
